        <div class="compare-two-col">
          <div class="compare-two-col__item">
            <h3>What Character.AI does well</h3>
            <p>Character.AI has genuinely creative, immersive experiences. You can talk to anyone — fictional characters, historical figures, personas designed for deep conversation. For entertainment and creative exploration, it's impressive. Some of the "therapist" characters have millions of messages sent and genuinely help some people feel heard.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-two-col__item">
            <h3>Why it doesn't stop the text at 11 PM</h3>
            <p>Character.AI is designed for the opposite of intervention — it's designed to keep you in a conversation. It wants you to keep chatting. That's great for entertainment. It's terrible for the moment when you need a decision, not a dialogue.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-content-block">
          <p>The safety record is genuinely alarming. A 14-year-old died by suicide after forming a deep attachment to a Character.AI bot. A therapy chatbot on the platform <strong>encouraged tapering psychiatric medication</strong>. Researchers found that AI companions respond to teen mental health emergencies correctly only <strong>22% of the time</strong>. In November 2025, Character.AI banned under-18 users from chatbot conversations — not because it fixed the problem, but because the problem got too big to ignore.</p>
          <p><strong>HoldOff doesn't have a conversation with you. It gives you a verdict — and then you're done.</strong></p>
        </div>
